{"updated_at": "2012-05-27T03:40:23Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-05-27T03:40:23Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5951218", "id": 5951218, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6499", "issue_id": 6499, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/jackdempsey", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "1ccb5123d1af92e24b32cec62abcf9a8", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/1ccb5123d1af92e24b32cec62abcf9a8?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd18f655c3fce66ca401d5f38b48c89af.png", "id": 479, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/events{/privacy}", "login": "jackdempsey", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jackdempsey/followers"}, "body": "Yeah this has always been a bit confusing. \n\nIMHO the important difference is:\n\n--full generates a rails engine meant to be included alongside the rest of your application. It's like it operates in the same style, but the files are elsewhere.\n\n--mountable generates a rails engine meant to be mounted at a certain isolated URL. \n\nSo --full is like continuing with your app but elsewhere, mountable is more a subcomponent you can embed into a variety of applications.", "_id": {"$oid": "52380761bd3543c15100ca91"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6499#issuecomment-5951218"}
